1 olive oil
egg
white wine vinegar
1 Potato
1 Kumara
1 Lamb Mince
1 Fine Breadcrumbs
1 Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
1 Sweetcorn
1 Celery
1 Parsley
1 Slaw Mix
2 Smokey Aioli

• Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Peel and cut the potato and kumara into bite-sized chunks.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle generously with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
TIP: Leave the kumara unpeeled if you prefer!

• Meanwhile, combine pork mince, fine breadcrumbs, mild Caribbean jerk seasoning and egg in a medium bowl.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of the pork mixture into small meatballs. Transfer to a plate. You should get 4-5 meatballs per person.
 ~~~~~~~~~~ MODULAR STEP ~~~~~~~~~~
• Meanwhile, combine lamb mince, fine breadcrumbs, mild Caribbean jerk seasoning and egg in a medium bowl.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of the lamb mixture into small meatballs. Transfer to a plate. You should get 4-5 meatballs per person.

• Drain the sweetcorn.
• Heat a large frying pan over a high heat. Cook the sweetcorn until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl.
TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are “popping” out.

• Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the meatballs, turning, until browned and cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
TIP: Don't worry if the meatballs char a little, this adds to the flavour!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery. Roughly chop parsley.
• Add the slaw mix, celery, parsley, 1/2 the smokey aioli and a drizzle of white wine vinegar to the charred corn. Season and toss to coat.

• Divide the jerk pork meatballs, roasted kumara and charred corn slaw between plates. Serve with the remaining smokey aioli. Enjoy!
 ~~~~~~~~~~ MODULAR STEP ~~~~~~~~~~
• Divide the jerk lamb meatballs, roasted kumara and charred corn slaw between plates. Serve with the remaining smokey aioli. Enjoy!